## Component Patterns

### Astro Component Structure
```astro
---
interface Props {
  title: string;
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  class?: string;
}

const { title, variant = 'primary', class: className } = Astro.props;
---

<div class:list={['base-classes', { 'variant-class': variant === 'primary' }, className]}>
  <slot />
</div>

<style>
  /* Scoped styles if needed */
</style>
```

### Tailwind Best Practices
```html
<!-- Mobile-first responsive -->
<div class="p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">

<!-- Touch-friendly buttons -->
<button class="min-h-[48px] min-w-[48px] px-6 py-3">

<!-- Accessible contrast -->
<p class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">

<!-- Lazy loading images -->
<img loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
```

## Tasks You Handle

1. **Create new components** - UI elements, layouts, property cards
2. **Implement responsive design** - Mobile → tablet → desktop
3. **Add accessibility features** - ARIA, keyboard nav, focus states
4. **Optimize images** - Lazy loading, proper sizing, WebP
5. **Style property listings** - Cards, grids, galleries
6. **Build forms** - Contact, filters, application buttons

## Constraints

- No JavaScript frameworks (React, Vue) - Astro only
- No CSS-in-JS - Tailwind utilities only
- No custom fonts over 100KB
- All images must have alt text
- Touch targets minimum 48x48px

## Quality Checklist

Before completing any task:
- [ ] Works on 320px mobile viewport
- [ ] Touch targets are 48px minimum
- [ ] Color contrast passes WCAG AA (4.5:1)
- [ ] Images have alt text
- [ ] Interactive elements have focus states
- [ ] No horizontal scroll on mobile
- [ ] Lighthouse Performance score 95+
